6static int
7dump_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
8{
9 struct dump_options opt;
10 int ret;
11 int optidx = 0;
12 struct getargs args[] = {
13 { "config-file", 'c', arg_string, NULL, "configuration file", "file" },
14 { "no-lock", 'n', arg_flag, NULL, "don't lock iprop log", NULL },
15 { "reverse", 'R', arg_flag, NULL, "dump the log in reverse order", NULL },
16 { "realm", 'r', arg_string, NULL, "realm", NULL },
17 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
18 };
19 int help_flag = 0;
20 opt.config_file_string = NULL;
21 opt.no_lock_flag = 0;
22 opt.reverse_flag = 0;
23 opt.realm_string = NULL;
24 args[0].value = &opt.config_file_string;
25 args[1].value = &opt.no_lock_flag;
26 args[2].value = &opt.reverse_flag;
27 args[3].value = &opt.realm_string;
28 args[4].value = &help_flag;
29 if(getarg(args, 5, argc, argv, &optidx))
30 goto usage;
31 if(argc - optidx > 1) {
32 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are more than expected (1).\n\n", argc - optidx);
33 goto usage;
34 }
35 if(help_flag)
36 goto usage;
37 ret = iprop_dump(&opt, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
38 return ret;
39usage:
40 arg_printusage (args, 5, "dump", "");
41 return 0;
42}

44static int
45truncate_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
46{
47 struct truncate_options opt;
48 int ret;
49 int optidx = 0;
50 struct getargs args[] = {
51 { "config-file", 'c', arg_string, NULL, "configuration file", "file" },
52 { "realm", 'r', arg_string, NULL, "realm", NULL },
53 { "keep-entries", 'K', arg_integer, NULL, "number of entries to keep", NULL },
54 { "max-bytes", 'B', arg_integer, NULL, "keep entries that fit in the given number of bytes", NULL },
55 { "reset", 'R', arg_flag, NULL, "reset the log to version 1; forces full propagation", NULL },
56 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
57 };
58 int help_flag = 0;
59 opt.config_file_string = NULL;
60 opt.realm_string = NULL;
61 opt.keep_entries_integer = -1;
62 opt.max_bytes_integer = -1;
63 opt.reset_flag = 0;
64 args[0].value = &opt.config_file_string;
65 args[1].value = &opt.realm_string;
66 args[2].value = &opt.keep_entries_integer;
67 args[3].value = &opt.max_bytes_integer;
68 args[4].value = &opt.reset_flag;
69 args[5].value = &help_flag;
70 if(getarg(args, 6, argc, argv, &optidx))
71 goto usage;
72 if(argc - optidx > 1) {
73 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are more than expected (1).\n\n", argc - optidx);
74 goto usage;
75 }
76 if(help_flag)
77 goto usage;
78 ret = iprop_truncate(&opt, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
79 return ret;
80usage:
81 arg_printusage (args, 6, "truncate", "");
82 return 0;
83}

85static int
86replay_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
87{
88 struct replay_options opt;
89 int ret;
90 int optidx = 0;
91 struct getargs args[] = {
92 { "start-version", 0, arg_integer, NULL, "start replay with this version", "version-number" },
93 { "end-version", 0, arg_integer, NULL, "end replay with this version", "version-number" },
94 { "config-file", 'c', arg_string, NULL, "configuration file", "file" },
95 { "realm", 'r', arg_string, NULL, "realm", NULL },
96 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
97 };
98 int help_flag = 0;
99 opt.start_version_integer = -1;
100 opt.end_version_integer = -1;
101 opt.config_file_string = NULL;
102 opt.realm_string = NULL;
103 args[0].value = &opt.start_version_integer;
104 args[1].value = &opt.end_version_integer;
105 args[2].value = &opt.config_file_string;
106 args[3].value = &opt.realm_string;
107 args[4].value = &help_flag;
108 if(getarg(args, 5, argc, argv, &optidx))
109 goto usage;
110 if(argc - optidx > 1) {
111 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are more than expected (1).\n\n", argc - optidx);
112 goto usage;
113 }
114 if(help_flag)
115 goto usage;
116 ret = iprop_replay(&opt, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
117 return ret;
118usage:
119 arg_printusage (args, 5, "replay", "");
120 return 0;
121}

186static int
187help_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
188{
189 int ret;
190 int optidx = 0;
191 struct getargs args[] = {
192 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
193 };
194 int help_flag = 0;
195 args[0].value = &help_flag;
196 if(getarg(args, 1, argc, argv, &optidx))
197 goto usage;
198 if(argc - optidx > 1) {
199 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are more than expected (1).\n\n", argc - optidx);
200 goto usage;
201 }
202 if(help_flag)
203 goto usage;
204 ret = help(NULL, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
205 return ret;
206usage:
207 arg_printusage (args, 1, "help", "command");
208 return 0;
209}
